<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,510,1512]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,335,1272,1296]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species is named for Keith S. Brown (Universidade Estadual de Campinas, São Paulo, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,223,1308,1332]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), who made important contributions about the genetic variation within the populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1435,1308,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1435,1308,1332]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Philaethria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
butterflies in South 
<collectingCountry box="[372,468,1344,1368]" name="United States of America" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">America</collectingCountry>
and suggested the existing of good sibling species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1189,1344,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dido">
<emphasis box="[1112,1189,1344,1368]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. dido</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,510,1512]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,495,1380,1405]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[502,608,1380,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni">
<emphasis box="[502,608,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. browni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs along the Cordillera de Merida (east slope) in the state of Barinas, between 
<quantity box="[252,393,1416,1440]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="900.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="600.0">600–1200 m</quantity>
in premontane forest habitats. 
<taxonomicName box="[743,850,1416,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="browni">
<emphasis box="[743,850,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. browni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flies sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1359,1416,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ostara" subSpecies="meridensis">
<emphasis box="[1131,1359,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. ostara meridensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neildi">P. neildi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
